article.headline: Buffalo 72, Canisius 69
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) -- Yassin Idbihi and Eric Moore each scored 20 points as Buffalo opened the season with a 72-69 win over cross-town rival Canisius Friday. Idbihi shot 8-of-12 from the floor with eight rebounds, while Moore went 6-of-11 from the floor, 4-of-7 from beyond the 3-point arc as Buffalo (1-0) spoiled the head coaching debut of Canisius' Tom Parrotta. Canisius (0-1) had its chance for the win, trailing by 70-69. Buffalo's Greg Gamble (10 points) missed a pair of free throws and Bret Wackerly grabbed the rebound for Canisius, which set up an inbounds play with just 9 seconds left. But Wackerly turned the ball over to Buffalo's John Boyer, who was then fouled with just two seconds left on the clock. Boyer drained a pair of free throws to seal the game. Darnell Wilson and Corey Herring led Canisius with 17 points each. Wilson was 8-of-12 from the floor while Herring went 6 for 14, 3-of-5 from beyond the arc with 3 rebounds and 4 assists before fouling out. Canisius' Pawel Malesa drained 4-of-9 3-point attempts for 12 points. Buffalo opened with a 12-point run which the Golden Griffins answered with a 12-3 stretch to pull even. Pawel Malesa's 3-pointer gave Canisius its first lead, 23-20 with 10:30 left in the first half. While both teams committed 14 turnovers in a sloppily played first half, Buffalo's Andy Robinson drained a 15-footer at the buzzer for a 34-34 tie at intermission. Buffalo shot 15-of-25 from the field while Canisius was 12-of-26. Buffalo shot 51.1 percent for the game (23 for 45) while the Golden Griffins went 24 for 55 (43.6 percent).
